The paper deals with the construction and analysis of locally decodable codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and distributed storage (cs.DS) communities. The paper also discusses the applications of locally decodable codes in probabilistically checkable proofs (cs.CC), cryptography (cs.CR), and coding theory (cs.DM). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
